doc.after: Greek mythology consists of stories belonging to the ancient Greeks concerning their gods and heroes the nature of the world and the origins and significance of their religious practices The main Greek gods were the twelve Olympians Zeus his wife Hera Poseidon Ares Hermes Hephaestus Aphrodite Athena Apollo Artemis Demeter and Dionysus Other important deities included Hebe Hades Helios Hestia Persephone and Heracles Zeus s parents were Cronus and Rhea who also were the parents of Poseidon Hades Hera Hestia and Demeter
